{"id":"mai-gnho","kind":"artifact","type":"artifact","status":"closed","title":"Session handoff: docs sync state and open issues","body":"## Current State (2026-03-28 23:15)\n\n### What works\n- `mai docs sync` on clean repos: import untracked .md files as doc notes, write doc notes to disk, bidirectional update via content hash — all tested with 14 adversarial tests + 3 fsnotify tests\n- `mai docs sync` on trek: returns 'Everything in sync' in 2.6s (cached), 75s cold rebuild\n- Daemon alive (pid 42582), watching 5 repos including trek\n- autoSyncDoc fires on every `mai create -k doc` when docs.sync=auto\n- Tombstones prevent resurrection of intentionally deleted doc files\n- File always wins on conflict (hash check before overwriting)\n\n### What's broken / incomplete\n\n**1. Trek has 27 untracked plan files in docs/**\nThese are real files from agents working on feature branches. They're untracked in git. If someone runs `mai docs sync` on trek, these 27 files WILL be imported as doc notes (the git-tracked check passes because they're untracked). This is correct behavior — but the user should know it's coming. Needs the --dry-run flag (mai-2q09).\n\n**2. Trek zombie doc notes — partially cleaned but uncertain**\nWe purged 907 zombie doc notes from trek's notes ref via Python script (direct git notes manipulation). 4441 noted objects remain. The purge removed kind:doc lines and events targeting doc IDs. BUT: we didn't verify the purge was complete — some zombie events may have survived if they didn't have edges pointing to known doc IDs. `mai doctor` should detect orphaned events.\n\n**3. No --dry-run for docs sync (mai-2q09)**\nCan't preview what sync WILL do before it does it. Critical for large repos.\n\n**4. No bulk cleanup command (mai-svwn)**\nWhen things go wrong (like the 907 zombie incident), there's no `mai purge` or `mai doctor --fix`. Had to write a custom Python script to surgically edit the notes ref. Need: `mai doctor --purge-kind=doc` or similar.\n\n**5. No confirmation for bulk operations (mai-jw7y)**\n`mai docs sync` on a repo with 342 existing docs will import them all with zero confirmation. Needs a prompt or summary before executing when \u003eN files affected.\n\n**6. docs sync output is a wall of text (mai-xjo9)**\n400+ lines of `→ path (written from note)` is unreadable. Should group by operation with headers and print summary first.\n\n**7. Cold index rebuild is 75s on trek (mai-058m)**\ngit cat-file called individually per noted object. Should use `git cat-file --batch` for bulk reads. Cached is 2.6s which is fine.\n\n**8. mai-plgs still open — slugified paths vs original paths**\nThe original bug report. Fixed by the git-tracked check (don't import tracked files), but the underlying issue remains: if someone creates a doc note without a --target edge, docTargetPath slugifies the title. The slug may not match what the user expects. Need: always require --target for doc notes, or derive path more carefully.\n\n**9. CRDT not wired into docs yet (mai-n5q3)**\npkg/crdt exists and works (tested), but SyncDocs still uses plain-text content hash comparison. When both note body AND file diverge (true conflict), it currently picks file-wins. CRDT would merge character-level. This is the P0 epic.\n\n**10. Daemon watches repo root, can be slow on large repos**\nFixed: daemon now watches root shallow + docs dir recursive. But `addDirRecursive` still walks the docs dir on startup, which is fine for most repos but could be slow if docs/ has thousands of files.\n\n### Open tickets (docs/sync related)\n- mai-n5q3 [P0] CRDT docs layer epic\n- mai-plgs [P0] slugified paths vs originals\n- mai-svwn [P1] no bulk cleanup after zombie docs\n- mai-jw7y [P2] no confirmation for bulk sync\n- mai-xjo9 [P2] sync output formatting\n- mai-2q09 [P2] no --dry-run for docs sync\n- mai-058m [P2] cold index rebuild perf\n\n### Key files\n- pkg/notes/docs.go — SyncDocs, writeDocFile, readDocFiles, isGitTracked, docTargetPath\n- cmd/mai/daemon.go — runDaemon, addDirRecursive\n- cmd/mai/daemon_proc.go — ensureDaemon (PID-only check)\n- cmd/mai/main.go — registerRepo (skips temp dirs)\n- test/docs_test.go, test/docs_adversarial_test.go, test/docs_daemon_fsnotify_test.go\n\n### Session changes committed\n- 3769a46: fix docs sync only imports git-untracked files\n- 4687fdd: revert to import untracked (correct behavior)\n- dda4596: CLI flag overhaul (-t=title, --type long-only, -l tags, -h help, unknown flags error)\n- bf8887a: updated all skills/README for new flags\n- 09ac108: mai-adr skill, deleted mai-decision\n- agent-skills d3c1ed2: updated 22 files across 14 skills\n- agent-skills f559441: deleted the-archivist\n- pi-extensions 68da5ec: tool.ts flag update","timestamp":"2026-03-29T04:57:23Z","branch":"main"}
